Are there many schools teaching swimming?

Well, in Vietnam, swimming schools are not extremely widespread, but they are quite common, especially in larger cities like Ho Chi Minh City or Hanoi. Many public swimming pools and private sports center offer lessons for both children and adults. However, in rural areas, such facilities are less available, and people tend to swim in natural bodies of water like rivers or lakes instead of attending formal classes. That said, the demand for swimming lessons is gradually increasing, particularly as parents become more concerned about water safety.

Do you think it is necessary for everyone to learn to swim?
Yes, I believe learning to swim is essential for most people. In a country like Vietnam, which has many rivers, canals, and a long coastline, swimming is an important life skill that can help prevent accidents and even save lives. In addition, it is an excellent form of exercise, as it improves overall fitness wihle being gentle on the joints. It is also a practical skill, especially in a hot climate, as people can use it to relax and cool off. Even for those who do not live near water, I still think it is a valuable skill to have, as unexpected situations can always arise.
